Arclib - library for writing command line interface (client)

This folder contains the framework for building command line interfaces. 
The following classes/files are present:

o ACC - Base class for Arc Client Components (plugins)
o ClientInterface - Sets up client side mcc chain
o Broker - Base class for Broker
o ExecutionTarget - Generic execution target (flattened glue2 structure)
o JobController - Base class for specialization (see src/hed/acc)
o Job - Generic representation of a job
o JobSupervisor - Responsible for loading JobControllers
o RandomBroker - Random Broker
o SmartBroker - Smart Broker
o Submitter - Base class for specialization (see src/hed/acc)
o TargeGenerator - Loads TargetRetrievers and performs resource discovery
o TargetRetriever - Base class for specialization (see src/hed/acc)
o UserConfig - Class for handling client configuration

See also the technical documentation and user guide:

doc/client

For command line interfaces built upon functionality contained within 
this library see

src/clients/arclib/


